WorkItem.ClosedComment: This would be difficult to implement, I'd rather we spend the time just getting Tree loading instead.Good suggestion though
WorkItem.Description:
It appears that druid.tree is not yet implemented.  This is perfectly understandable, and clearly listed in the model status page.
 
However, it takes a while to find that page, and the indication that its not implemented in the app is pretty subtle - you select it, but "nothing happens" : the model indicator at the bottom right doesn't change.  It appears to be "buglike" instead of intentional. At least, it took me a bit to figure out what was going on.
 
Can I suggest that the menu be disabled and a not-yet-implemented tag be added to those models that don't exist, like in import menu?
